{
  "_readme": "This is the COMPLETE structure for an Orient AC remote — every button a typical split-AC remote has, correctly named and formatted. The 'pattern' fields are null because real IR codes cannot be invented — they must be captured once from your physical Orient remote (see capture/OrientIRCapture.ino). Replace each null with the numbers you capture, flip 'captured' to true, and this file is done. Once filled in, run scripts/export_to_flipper_ir.py to convert it into a .ir file you can import directly into IR Blaster Remote.",
  "device": "Orient Air Conditioner",
  "protocol_note": "Almost certainly a 'raw' state-based protocol (not a simple NEC code) — this is normal for AC remotes and is exactly what type: raw / data captures.",
